Insertion Sort –:

Insertion Sort is a simple sorting algorithm that works by taking one element at a time and inserting it into its correct position in the already sorted part of 
the array. It is similar to the way we sort playing cards in our hand.

Key Points :-

---->The array is divided into sorted and unsorted parts.

----->It picks one element from the unsorted part.

----->Inserts it into the correct position in the sorted part.

----->Works efficiently for small datasets or nearly sorted arrays.

Time Complexity

Best Case: O(n) (when array is already sorted)

Average Case: O(n²)

Worst Case: O(n²)

Space Complexity

O(1) (in-place sorting)

Example

Array: 8, 3, 5, 2

Pass 1
Key = 3
Compare with 8 → shift 8
Array → 3, 8, 5, 2

Pass 2
Key = 5
Compare with 8 → shift 8
Insert after 3
Array → 3, 5, 8, 2

Pass 3
Key = 2
Shift 8, 5, 3
Insert at start
Array → 2, 3, 5, 8

Sorted Array → 2, 3, 5, 8

Java Code
class InsertionSort {
    static void insertionSort(int arr[]) {
        int n = arr.length;

        for(int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            int key = arr[i];
            int j = i - 1;

            while(j >= 0 && arr[j] > key) {
                arr[j + 1] = arr[j];
                j--;
            }

            arr[j + 1] = key;
        }
    }
}
